Package ohos.security.asset

Class AssetOperator

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.security.asset.AssetOperator

  • public class AssetOperator
extends Object
    Implements the AssetOperatorAbs interfaces and provides the capability of storing key asset data.

    The AssetOperator interfaces can be used to securely store, delete, update, and query key asset data, such as usernames and passwords.

    This class implements the AssetOperatorAbs abstract class. For details about the abstract methods, see AssetOperatorAbs.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.security.asset

      • INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_SELECT_MODE

        public static final String INTENT_PARAMS_KEY_SELECT_MODE
        Indicates the query mode.

        This constant can be used to set the exact or batch query mode when the AssetOperatorAbs#assetSelect(Ability, IntentParams) interface is called. The constant value can be SELECT_ONCE, SELECT_FROM_BEGIN, or SELECT_CONTINUE.

      • getInstance

        public static AssetOperatorAbs getInstance​()
        Obtains an AssetOperatorAbs instance in the singleton pattern.

        You can use the obtained instance to invoke the abstract methods of the AssetOperatorAbs abstract class. You cannot use the new method to create instances.

        Returns:
        Returns the AssetOperatorAbs instance.
